{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id053f2b07-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1462"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1462"},"text":"§ 1462.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Forfeiture ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002020"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002020"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See Codification note below."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"If such ","children":[{"tag":"sup","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" owner, agent, or other person shall fail to comply with his demand, the officer "},{"tag":"sup","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" shall retain such trunk, traveling bag, sack, valise, or other container or closed vehicle, and open the same, and, as soon thereafter as may be practicable, examine the contents, and if any article subject to duty or any article the importation of which is prohibited is found therein, the whole contents and the container or vehicle shall be subject to forfeiture."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id053f2b08-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497"},"text":"June 17, 1930, ch. 497","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 462, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/718"},"text":"46 Stat. 718","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id053f2b09-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id053f2b0a-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id053f2b0b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As enacted by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", the catchline for this section was “Same—forfeiture”, as this section was intended to be read as a continuation of the provisions introduced in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1459"},"text":"section 1459 of this title","children":[],"tail":". When first enacted, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1459"},"text":"section 1459 of this title","children":[],"tail":" related to arrival in the United States from a contiguous country but has since been amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570","children":[],"tail":" to relate to arrival more generally. The uses of “such” and “the officer” in text are meant to refer back to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1461"},"text":"section 1461 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id053f2b0c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in R.S. § 3101, which was superseded by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/tIV/s462"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356, title IV, § 462","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/956"},"text":"42 Stat. 956","children":[],"tail":", and was repealed by section 642 thereof. Section 462 of the 1922 act was superseded by section 462 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", comprising this section, and repealed by section 651(a)(1) of the 1930 act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
